    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Courier Sorting Using Information Stored In Qr Code</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Abhinav Saxena, Akhilesh Kumar Singh<br />Amit Kumar Das, Anurag Mahto</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Courier Sorting<br />Information Stored In Qr Code</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5504</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">In the past few years, increasing opportunities of careers in big cities has been experienced; resulting in migration of people from different parts of a country to big metropolitan cities. Today a lot of families could be seen with all members in different parts of the country or even world. Hence to keep the family tied it has been seen that gifts, cards, greetings and even eatables are sent to each other via post or courier service.
In the process of facilitating these couriers a lot of stages are involved such as registration, collection, sorting, dispatching and distribution. In sorting the couriers are kept in different sections depending on the city to which they are to be sent. Mostly in courier industry these processes are carried by men and hence there are possibilities of error being committed. A slightest error can divert a route of a courier by hundreds of kilometers.
Hence there is a need to automate to prevent any such miss happening. This could be achieved by marking the couriers with an automatic readable tag. These could be bar code, RFID tag or QR code. The QR code stands for Quick response code and is composed of black and white matrices made up by squares. The name or the address of the destination is stored as pattern on the QR code. The QR code is advantageous over other techniques as they are faster in getting read and no aligning with the camera is needed. It could be read at any angle, even inverted.
The automated system consists of a conveyor on which the courier is placed by the operator with the QR code facing the camera so that it could be read. The conveyor keeps on moving up to the time when an Infrared sensor detects an object. The conveyor ensuring that the courier is read correctly. The QR code is decoded and the string with city name is generated and sent to arduino through serial interface which then moves the flapper and guides the flapper to destination city collection point</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9525">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9525</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/8768">EIE-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
